    <section class="panel capital-section" id="funding">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label">Funding</p>
          <h2>Fox Point already has $5 million in pledges.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="section-copy">This site does not need a new pitch. It needs design, permits, planning, and people working together so the money already linked to Fox Point can be put to work.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="capital-stack">
        <article class="capital-row">
          <div class="capital-meta">
            <p class="capital-amount">$2.5M</p>
            <p class="capital-source">Heffernan Bond Bill</p>
            <span class="status-chip status-contingent">Not active yet</span>
          </div>
          <div class="capital-detail">
            <h3>Wetland and park work</h3>
            <p>Rep. Heffernan pledged $3M in bond funding to help meet state environmental requirements for the new Edgemoor port. Of that, $2.5M is set aside for wetland and park work at Fox Point. It would move when port construction starts and the Diamond State Port Corporation approves it.</p>
            <div class="capital-bar-track">
              <div class="capital-bar-fill capital-bar-heff"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="capital-row">
          <div class="capital-meta">
            <p class="capital-amount">$1.725M</p>
            <p class="capital-source">DNREC restoration funds</p>
            <span class="status-chip status-identified">In state plan</span>
          </div>
          <div class="capital-detail">
            <h3>Fox Point Cove wetland restoration</h3>
            <p>The January 9, 2025 state plan names Fox Point Cove as the project site. It covers wetland work, erosion control near the wharf, design, and permits. If money is left over, it could support more restoration or later upkeep.</p>
            <div class="capital-bar-track">
              <div class="capital-bar-fill capital-bar-apu"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="capital-row">
          <div class="capital-meta">
            <p class="capital-amount">$808K</p>
            <p class="capital-source">DuPont Hay Road / NOAA settlement</p>
            <span class="status-chip status-future">Not assigned yet</span>
          </div>
          <div class="capital-detail">
            <h3>Future restoration money from a pollution settlement</h3>
            <p>This money comes from a NOAA settlement tied to the DuPont Hay Road site near Edgemoor. NOAA leads the process. No project site has been chosen yet, but Fox Point fits the kind of work this money could support.</p>
            <div class="capital-bar-track">
              <div class="capital-bar-fill capital-bar-chem"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <div class="capital-total-row">
          <div class="capital-total-bar" role="img" aria-label="$5.03 million total: $2.5M bond bill, $1.725M DNREC restoration funds, and $808K from the DuPont Hay Road NOAA settlement">
            <div class="ctb-segment ctb-heff">$2.5M</div>
            <div class="ctb-segment ctb-apu">$1.725M</div>
            <div class="ctb-segment ctb-chem">$808K</div>
          </div>
          <div class="capital-total-label-row">
            <span class="ctb-legend"><span class="ctb-dot ctb-heff-dot"></span>Bond Bill</span>
            <span class="ctb-legend"><span class="ctb-dot ctb-apu-dot"></span>DNREC plan</span>
            <span class="ctb-legend"><span class="ctb-dot ctb-chem-dot"></span>Hay Road settlement</span>
